# Terminal Calculator

A simple calculator application built with Node.js that runs directly in the terminal.

## Features

* Addition
* Subtraction
* Multiplication
* Division
* Reset current value
* Exit program
* Input validation for invalid numbers
* Prevent division by zero

## Technologies Used

* JavaScript
* Node.js
* Readline module

## Project Structure

```text
project-folder/
│
├── calculator.js
└── README.md
```

## How to Run

1. Install Node.js on your computer.
2. Open the terminal.
3. Navigate to the project folder.
4. Run the following command:

```bash
node calculator.js
```

## Example Usage

```text
Choose an operator: +, -, *, /, reset, exit
> +

Enter a number:
> 10

Current value: 10

Choose an operator: +, -, *, /, reset, exit
> *

Enter a number:
> 5

Current value: 50
```

## Available Commands

| Command | Description              |
| ------- | ------------------------ |
| +       | Add a number             |
| -       | Subtract a number        |
| *       | Multiply by a number     |
| /       | Divide by a number       |
| reset   | Reset current value to 0 |
| exit    | Close the calculator     |

## Error Handling

* If the user enters an invalid number, the program will display an error message.
* If the user tries to divide by 0, the calculator will show an error message.
* If the user enters an invalid operator, the program will ask again.

## Future Improvements

* Add support for decimal numbers
* Add calculation history
* Save history to a file
